1
00:00:07,389 --> 00:00:11,993
So that something sweet
can be produced from tears.

2
00:00:12,083 --> 00:00:13,493
[Mother Mary’s Tears]

3
00:00:13,493 --> 00:00:16,744
When we were in Hungary
in the Summer,

4
00:00:16,744 --> 00:00:22,850
somehow this flower 
came to us,

5
00:00:22,850 --> 00:00:30,129
and it’s called, I believe the name is,
Lily of the Valley,

6
00:00:30,129 --> 00:00:37,613
and it has 
some extraordinary fragrance.

7
00:00:37,613 --> 00:00:43,131
So there, I remember, 
many of these places

8
00:00:43,131 --> 00:00:48,698
they’ve been retrofitted 
with Christianity,

9
00:00:48,698 --> 00:00:51,678
although they may have been
Pagans previously.

10
00:00:51,678 --> 00:00:56,283
But one of the legends there
about this flower

11
00:00:56,283 --> 00:01:00,865
is that it was created
from the tears of Mary

12
00:01:00,865 --> 00:01:04,091
at the crucifixion of Jesus,

13
00:01:04,091 --> 00:01:06,901
that her tears 
went into the soil

14
00:01:06,901 --> 00:01:14,049
and these flowers sprung up
as a result of those tears.

15
00:01:14,809 --> 00:01:21,678
So, that tears
can produce something sweet,

16
00:01:21,678 --> 00:01:26,570
that requires a different type
of thinking.

